-- National Bank of Canada Tower in Montreal Blocked
-- B y   F r e d e r i c   T o m e s c o
-- 2012-04-11T13:14:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/national-bank-of-canada-tower-in-montreal-blocked.html
Employees working in the  National
Bank of Canada  tower in downtown  Montreal  have been allowed into
the building after police broke up a demonstration blocking
access to the structure.  About 200 protesters had earlier gathered in front of the
building on De La Gauchetiere street, RDI television reported.
Students were demonstrating against a planned increase in
university tuition fees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frederic Tomesco in Montreal at 
 tomesco@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jacqueline Thorpe at 
